    "history" -> {"14.1", "14.3", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiJump[{..., {v i 1, v i 2, ...} -> si, ...}] represents a set of \
quantum jump operators li in terms of dressed Dirac fermion modes di = \
\\[CapitalSigma]j vij cj, where cj are Majorana fermion operators cj. The \
jump operator li = di if si = 0; li = d_i^\\[Dagger] if si = 1; li = \
d_i^\\[Dagger] di if si = 2 and li = di d_i^\\[Dagger] if si = 3. Setting si \
= 4 implies a set of two jump operators d_i^\\[Dagger] di and di \
d_i^\\[Dagger]. BravyiJump[msr] converts BravyiMeasurement object msr to \
BravyiJump object. With the option Completion -> True, each row v in msr are \
converted to {v -> 2, v -> 3} (corresponding to the nonselective \
measurement); or v -> 2 otherwise.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "BravyiJump", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "BravyiJump", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiJump"}},
